text: sean the laser class teacher mentioned a new thing at ADX: every other thursday (the weeks there isn't a cert class) he's putting on a lab. The idea is that you bring in some experimental designs or materials and experiment with the laser (for free) getting everything set so you can run your final design with no surprises.
sounds kind of cool so I'm going to be there next week
oh and there's also the option to use the laser cutter to actually cut out your final design during the lab. $2/min. so might make sense for small projects vs. $25 per 30 minute block

Reminds me so much of when I had to print designs in my school's fancy printer. Spent so much money on time used and wasted materials the first couple of times I used it. After that it was fairly quick and cheap.
